Class LinkedListRecursive<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.util.LinkedListRecursive<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - is the generic object that the list will be made from

    public class LinkedListRecursive<E>
extends java.lang.Object
    Custom implementation of a recursive linked list that doesn’t allow for null elements or duplicate elements as defined by the equals() method.

      • add

        public boolean add(E object)
        Method checks that the element isn’t already in the list (an IllegalArgumentException is thrown if the element already exists) and handles the special case of adding a node to an empty list. If the list is not empty, then the public method transfers the flow of control to the private ListNode.add(E element) method, which completes the recursion to add to element to the end of the list.
        Parameters:
        object - is the object that is added if it is not a duplicate in the list
        Returns:
        true if the object is added

        If the element is added to the middle or end of the list, then the public method transfers the flow of control to the private ListNode.add(int index, E element) method, which completes the recursion to add to element at the appropriate location.

        index - is the position that the object will be added
        object - is the object that will be placed at that position
